abel\";s:18:\"Download for Linux\";s:4:\"name\";s:18:\"download_for_linux\";s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"file\";s:12:\"instructions\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"required\";s:1:\"0\";s:12:\"column_width\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"save_format\";s:3:\"url\";s:7:\"library\";s:3:\"all\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:11;}}s:7:\"row_min\";s:0:\"\";s:9:\"row_limit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"layout\";s:3:\"row\";s:12:\"button_label\";s:11:\"Add Species\";s:17:\"conditional_logic\";a:3:{s:6:\"status\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"rules\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"field\";s:4:\"null\";s:8:\"operator\";s:2:\"==\";}}s:8:\"allorany\";s:3:\"all\";}s:8:\"order_no\";i:2;}'),(46,14,'description','The myKrobe predictor is designed for use by doctors. It analyses the whole genome of a bacterial sample and provides the information a doctor needs in order to choose a treatment, all within a couple of minutes. No expertise is needed to run or interpret it, and it works on a standard desktop or laptop.'),(47,14,'_description','field_534e14b5161c9'),(48,14,'screenshot',''),(49,14,'_screenshot','field_534e14cf08e27'),(50,14,'species_0_title','S.Aureus'),(51,14,'_species_0_title','field_534e152766e4b'),(52,14,'species_0_description','Our first (beta) release is the predictor for Staphylococcus. Given a blood culture sample which is positive for Gram stain, the myKrobe predictor will determine which species the sample is, and if Staphylococcus aureus, it will predict the resistance profile for 12 key antibiotics, including quinoloines, macrolides/lincosamides, beta-lactams and tetracyclines.'),(53,14,'_species_0_description','field_534e153a66e4c'),(54,14,'species_0_small_print','Technical specs: Runs on Windows and Linux, requires ~500Mb of RAM, takes between 40 seconds and 3 minutes to run Sequencing: Supports Illumina and Oxford Nanopore Technology sequencing data. Antibiotics supported: Beta-lactams (methicillin, penicillin), quinolones (ciprofloxacin), macrolides/lincosamides (erythromycin, clindamycin), tetracycline, aminoglycosides (gentamicin), glycopeptides (vancomycin), rifampicin, mupirocin, fusidic acid, trimethoprim. Predictive performance: Although not yet certified for clinical use, our tests on 992 samples show false negative rate of 0.3% (predicting susceptible when actually resistant) and false positive rate of 0.5% (predicting resistant when susceptible) which are below the requirements for FDA approval. See our paper for details.'),(55,14,'_species_0_small_print','field_534e154566e4d'),(56,14,'species','1'),(57,14,'_species','field_534e14fc5dcdc'),(58,10,'description','The myKrobe predictor is designed for use by microbiologists and doctors, and is designed to provide the information a physician needs in order to choose a treatment. The predictor analyses the whole genome of a bacterial sample, all within a couple of minutes. No expertise is needed to run or interpret it, and it works on a standard desktop or laptop.'),(59,10,'_description','field_534e14b5161c9'),(60,10,'screenshot','48'),(61,10,'_screenshot','field_534e14cf08e27'),(62,10,'species_0_title','S.Aureus'),(63,10,'_species_0_title','field_534e152766e4b'),(64,10,'species_0_description','Our first (beta) release is the predictor for <em>Staphylococcus</em>. Given a blood culture sample which is positive for Gram stain, the myKrobe predictor will determine which species the sample is, and if <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em>, it will predict the resistance profile for 12 key antibiotics, including quinolones, macrolides/lincosamides, beta-lactams and tetracyclines. It will also test for the presence of Panton-Valentin Leukocidin toxin.'),(65,10,'_species_0_description','field_534e153a66e4c'),(66,10,'species_0_small_print','Runs on Windows and Linux, requires ~500Mb of RAM, takes between 40 seconds and 3 minutes to run\r\n\r\nSequencing: Supports Illumina and Oxford Nanopore Technology sequencing data. Antibiotics supported: Beta-lactams (methicillin, penicillin), quinolones (ciprofloxacin), macrolides/lincosamides (erythromycin, clindamycin), tetracycline, aminoglycosides (gentamicin), glycopeptides (vancomycin), rifampicin, mupirocin, fusidic acid, trimethoprim.\r\n\r\nPredictive performance: Although not yet certified for clinical use, our tests on 992 samples show false negative rate of 0.3% (predicting susceptible when actually resistant) and false positive rate of 0.5% (predicting resistant when susceptible) which are below the requirements for FDA approval. See our paper for details.'),(67,10,'_species_0_small_print','field_534e154566e4d'),(68,10,'species','1'),(69,10,'_species','field_534e14fc5dcdc'),(71,15,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(72,15,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(73,15,'_menu_item_object_id','10'),(74,15,'_menu_item_object','page'),(75,15,'_menu_item_target',''),(76,15,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(77,15,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(78,15,'_menu_item_url',''),(80,16,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(81,16,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(82,16,'_menu_item_object_id','4'),(83,16,'_menu_item_object','page'),(84,16,'_menu_item_target',''),(85,16,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(86,16,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(87,16,'_menu_item_url',''),(89,17,'_edit_last','1'),(90,17,'_edit_lock','1400082405:1'),(91,17,'_wp_page_template','template-about.php'),(92,19,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(93,19,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(94,19,'_menu_item_object_id','17'),(95,19,'_menu_item_object','page'),(96,19,'_menu_item_target',''),(97,19,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(98,19,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(99,19,'_menu_item_url',''),(101,20,'_menu_item_type','custom'),(102,20,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(103,20,'_menu_item_object_id','20'),(104,20,'_menu_item_object','custom'),(105,20,'_menu_item_target',''),(106,20,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(107,20,'_menu_item_xfn',''),(108,20,'_menu