5354a337f7d9b'),(584,68,'species_0_description','Our first (beta) release is the predictor for <em>Staphylococcus</em>. Given a blood culture sample which is positive for Gram stain, the myKrobe predictor will determine which species the sample is, and if <em>Staphylococcus aureus</em>, it will predict the resistance profile for 12 key antibiotics, including quinolones, macrolides/lincosamides, beta-lactams and tetracyclines. It will also test for the presence of Panton-Valentin Leukocidin toxin.'),(585,68,'_species_0_description','field_534e153a66e4c'),(586,68,'species_0_small_print','Runs on Windows and Linux, requires ~500Mb of RAM, takes between 40 seconds and 3 minutes to run\r\n\r\nSequencing: Supports Illumina and Oxford Nanopore Technology sequencing data. Antibiotics supported: Beta-lactams (methicillin, penicillin), quinolones (ciprofloxacin), macrolides/lincosamides (erythromycin, clindamycin), tetracycline, aminoglycosides (gentamicin), glycopeptides (vancomycin), rifampicin, mupirocin, fusidic acid, trimethoprim.\r\n\r\nPredictive performance: Although not yet certified for clinical use, our tests on 992 samples show false negative rate of 0.3% (predicting susceptible when actually resistant) and false positive rate of 0.5% (predicting resistant when susceptible) which are below the requirements for FDA approval. See our paper for details.'),(587,68,'_species_0_small_print','field_534e154566e4d'),(588,68,'species_0_small_print_attachment','38'),(589,68,'_species_0_small_print_attachment','field_535637f3c9b5c'),(590,68,'species_0_small_print_attachment_title','White Paper'),(591,68,'_species_0_small_print_attachment_title','field_53563818c9b5d'),(592,68,'species_0_license_agreement','myKrobe predictor is free for non-commercial use. For commercial-use, please contact <a href=\"mailto:zam@mykrobe.com\">zam@mykrobe.com</a>. The software is not certified for clinical use, and we accept no liability.'),(593,68,'_species_0_license_agreement','field_535646c067